<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">The Assistant Director
of Internal Audit and Counter Fraud introduced the report. The
reporting process was explained, a summary on outcomes would be
presented to the Committee and subsequently at the next meeting the
relevant director would then attend to provide an update on
recommendations arising and progress made within their directorate.
The appendix demonstrated that there had been good progress across
all actions and the Assistant Director of Internal Audit and
Counter Fraud felt confident that the actions were moving in the
right directions.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">In response to
questions on absence management training, it was explained that the
training continued to be rolled out on a directorate-by-directorate
basis. Sickness absences were recorded electronically on Oracle.
The Director of HR and Organisational Development would provide the
Committee with the exact number of managers that had been trained
and would also provide a completion percentage rate.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">The Chair noted the
progress made and felt reassured that Lambeth was not alone, as
this was a challenge faced by many local authorities. The Chair
thanked officers for their work to date.</span></p>
