<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">The Risk Manager introduced the
report. It was noted that the Risk Management Strategy and Policy
were in their final year and would be fully updated for 2027-2030.
No major changes had been made as part of the annual review,
however, there has been some updates, which are set out in
paragraph 1.5 of the cover report.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">In response to Members&rsquo;
questions, it was explained that:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top:0cm">
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">Risk management
training, consisting of five e-learning modules, was available to
staff and Members on the intranet. Members would receive training
following the election;</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top:0cm">
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">The strategy and
policy were refreshed every three years, and the 2027-2030 strategy
would be presented to the Audit and Risk Committee for approval
later in the year;</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">The refreshed
strategy would cover corporate and directorate risks, risk appetite
and risk maturity;</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">The risk appetite was
last set in 2018-2019. Plans are in place to update and re-launch
our risk appetite statement and methodology during
2026;</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">Risk threats and
opportunities had previously been included, but the Council had
moved to a more threat-focused approach in recent
years;</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">JCAD was the
web-based system used to record and manage risks.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="">RESOLVED:</span></b>
<span style="">Corporate Committee considered and approved the risk
management strategy and policy 2023-2026 annual review.</span></p>
