<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">The Risk Manager introduced the report and
explained that the report provided an overview of the most recently
updated corporate risks. Risks were recorded on the JCAD system and
updated quarterly. Appendix 8 set out the top risks, which relate
to finance, cyber security, emergency planning and workforce. There
was a process in place to identify, assess and mitigate risks, with
each risk assigned to an owner. Future reports would provide
further assurance on day-to-day risk management. It was recommended
that each directorate be given the opportunity to attend a
Corporate Committee meeting to present their top risks.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Assistant Director of Internal Audit and
Counter Fraud noted that the risk spotlight item currently on the
work programmed had not operated as intended. It was suggested that
this slot be repurposed for directorates to present assurance on
their top ten risks, providing better oversight, a wider range of
assurance, and direct access to risk owners.<span style=
"">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Chair and the Committee Members agreed
that the risk spotlight item was not always effective and welcomed
the proposed reporting approach. Members also requested further
assurance that the policy was being followed and that staff
understood their responsibilities regarding risk.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><b>RESOLVED:</b> That the Committee:</p>
<ol start="1" style="margin-top:0cm">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">Considered the updated key risks at
quarter 3 2025/26.</li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">Considered and unanimously agreed
that each directorate presents its most significant risks for
oversight and assurance to the Committee on a cyclical basis to
ensure the Committee received assurance on a wider range of
directorate level risks.</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div> 
					
