<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">The Assistant Director of
Internal Audit and Counter Fraud (IACF) introduced the report. It
was noted that there had been an improvement on delivery and
engagement with management on internal audit activity. Several
audits had been completed with only a small number likely to be
rolled into the new financial year. He confirmed that his assurance
opinion was balanced and that the Council was moving in a positive
direction, with implementation rates improving from 54% at the end
of 2024-2025 to 84% during 2025-2026.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">In response to Members&rsquo;
questions, it was explained that:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style=""><span style="">&middot;<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<span style="">Maintained schools and nurseries faced financial
viability issues, and an oversight group had been established to
seek to address these challenges;</span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style=""><span style="">&middot;<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<span style="">The Assistant Director for IACF confirmed that he
was an active member on the Loughborough Estate Management Board
(LEMB) task and finish group;</span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style=""><span style="">&middot;<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<span style="">He was unable to discuss LEMB in detail due to
ongoing legal proceedings;</span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style=""><span style="">&middot;<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<span style="">Financial and regulatory actions were in place to
improve activities within LEMB and other Tenant Management
Organisations (TMOs);</span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style=""><span style="">&middot;<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<span style="">The Council continued to lobby central government
for stronger modular management agreements to support earlier
intervention when TMOs underperformed;</span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style=""><span style="">&middot;<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<span style="">A letter had also been sent to the Housing Minister
requesting improvements to this process;</span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style=""><span style="">&middot;<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<span style="">TMOs were audited every three years, and legally
could not be reviewed more frequently;</span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style=""><span style="">&middot;<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<span style="">Work was ongoing relating to safeguarding homes and
the private sector.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">The Assistant Director for IACF
explained that there was an update on the corporate health and
safety audit; however, the relevant Corporate Director had not
attended due to an administrative error with the meeting
invitation.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">The Committee requested a more
detailed response on the group that were supporting maintained
schools and nurseries, including its impact. The Assistant Director
agreed to discuss this with the Corporate Director of Children,
Families and Education and provide further information on
governance and managing financial deficits.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="">The Chair requested that
Corporate Directors be invited to all meetings of the Committee to
provide a comprehensive update to the Committee. The Acting Cabinet
Member for Finance also expressed her disappointed at the absence
of the relevant Corporate Director but thanked the Assistant
Director of IACF on the amount of work that had taken place on
Internal audit and the level of improvement that has been
demonstrated over recent months.</span></p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal"><span style=
"">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="">RESOLVED:</span></b>
<span style="">Corporate Committee considered progress made against
the 2025/26 Internal Audit plan as well as progress with the
implementation of management actions and were assured.</span></p>
</div>
</div> 
					
        </td>
