<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">The Head of Counter
Fraud introduced the report, it was noted that this was a standard
progress update report. The Council had secured a further 19
properties this month, which was ahead of target. Training for
contract managers of fraud awareness continued, and the peer review
details requested at a previous Committee meeting had been
referenced in the report.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">In response to
Members&rsquo; questions, it was explained that:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top:0cm">
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">The timeline for
recovering a property varied depending on the complexity and
circumstances of each case;</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">If a tenant agreed to
surrender the property, recovery could be achieved within
weeks;</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">Where a tenant did
not agree to leave, the Council would have to pursue civil recovery
through the courts, which could take up to 12 months;</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">Lambeth worked with
the National Fraud Initiative (NFI) and the London Fraud Hub, which
involved 26 London boroughs sharing agency and payroll data to
identify potential cases of individuals holding secondary jobs in
another borough;</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">NFI was still being
rolled out nationally, and all Council&rsquo;s would be required to
join;</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">Members congratulated
the team on the successful peer review and asked future reports
include the different types of internal fraud cases. The Chair
referred to recent news articles on &ldquo;polygamous
working&rdquo; and she felt reassured that the Council were part of
the NFI in order to identify this, she felt that a driver for this
was the working from home culture that came about during
COVID.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="">RESOLVED:</span></b>
<span style="">Corporate Committee considered the progress and
outcomes of the counter fraud activity for 2025/26 and the
Committee unanimously agreed to receive the updated Counter Fraud
Strategy at the March 2026 meeting.</span> <span style=
"">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
</div> 
					
