<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">The report was introduced by the Director of
HR and Organisational Development (OD) who presented the Committee
with a statement on the Council&rsquo;s Pay Policy. She confirmed
that the statement fulfilled statutory requirements and highlighted
that the Chief Executive&rsquo;s pay was subject to the national
frameworks, and that senior officers did not receive bonuses or
performance-based pay. The statement set out the relationship
between the lowest and highest paid employees in the Council, with
the Chief Executive making 4.8X the median salary, and 7.6X the
lowest paid employee&rsquo;s salary. The Director of HR and OD
clarified that no average multiple exists regarding pay generally,
but that Lambeth is in good keeping with its nearest neighbours. It
was also clarified that the statement must be approved by Full
Council and that its changes would take full effect in 2026/7
following this.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">In response to Member&rsquo;s questions, it
was explained that:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<ul style="margin-top:0cm">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">The decrease in the pay ratio was
not indicative of a greater number of lower-paid employees.</li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">The current Chief Executive&rsquo;s
pay is greater than that of his predecessor.</li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">The gender pay differential had
decreased compared to last year.</li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">The Inner London Weighting Allowance
was incorporated into Council salaries.</li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">The lowest-paid figure earned more
than they did last year, but the median figure had relatively
stayed the same.</li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Chair thanked the Director of HR and OD
for presenting the Statement and concluded the report.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><b>RESOLVED:</b> The Committee unanimously
agreed to recommend the Pay Policy Statement to Full Council for
approval on 04 March 2026.</p>
</div>
</div> 
					
